com.aylanetworks.aylasdk

类 AylaSchedule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaSchedule
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class AylaSchedule
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    AylaSchedule objects are used to set schedules on devices. Schedules may be configured in many ways, and can fire AylaScheduleActions at the start or end of the schedule cycle.

    AylaSchedules may not be created or destroyed, but rather are provided to devices via the device template when the device is registered.

    Schedules for a particular device may be obtained via AylaDevice.fetchSchedules(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaSchedule[]>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener)

      • hasFixedActions

        public boolean hasFixedActions()
        When a Schedule has fixedActions value as true it means the Schedule already has Schedule actions and the user cannot add any new Schedule actions. For fixedActions the user can only edit the existing Schedule Actions
